CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 12, 1966, pg. 2A, reads: "As Dr. King Visited Pittsburgh - These were scenes as Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., leader of the American Civil Rights Movement, visited Pittsburgh for a speech, a press conference, and a student question-and-answer session at the University of Pittsburgh's Student Union last week. Dr. King is shown in far left photo being officially welcomed by James McCoy, chairman of the United Negro Protest Committee and vice-chairman for the Pittsburgh NAACP, as the national civil rights leader arrived at the Student Union headquarters... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. shaking hands with James McCoy Jr., with Mike Desmond on his right, surrounded by men and women, including Charles Harris and Matthew Moore, at University of Pittsburgh Student Union
